**Explanation:** The Phillips-Perron (PP) test automatically corrects for autocorrelation and heteroskedasticity in the residuals of the unit root regression, unlike the Dickey-Fuller (DF) test, which assumes homoskedastic and serially uncorrelated errors. This makes PP more robust to these violations. The DF test does not account for these issues without manual adjustments.
